  "text": "Skull-base osteomyelitis arises mainly through secondary infection of malignant external otitis. Although skull-base osteomyelitis and malignant external otitis are considered to be identical concepts in many studies, it is more appropriate to conceive of and think about skull-base osteomyelitis with basal bone involvement in pathophysiological terms [CITATION_1] .",
